    "However, this variability is often excluded from the training dataset, introducing noise from inconsistent annotations or conflicting criteria, which can distort the target model's learning of desirable preference patterns.",
    "Similar issues may arise when using large language models (LLMs) for annotation as they exhibit human-like patterns (Bubeck et al., 2023).",
    "Chen et al. (2024a) observed that GPT-4 (Ope-nAI, 2023) can display inconsistent behavior during multi-step reasoning despite its impressive performance on various tasks.",
    "To mitigate these challenges arising from noisy data in the training dataset, manual data cleansing or adding additional annotations, such as the significance level of each preference data point, can be used (Touvron et al., 2023).",
    "However, these approaches are costly and time-consuming."
